        <div><a name="cls-7.9" id="cls-7.9"></a><h2>7.9<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Radar Wave Length</h2>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 7-9&#xA0;&#x2014; Radar Wave Length</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;"><a name="_20fb4994-907d-dccb-41b9-a17a11494c4a" id="_20fb4994-907d-dccb-41b9-a17a11494c4a"></a><tbody><tr><td valign="top" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;"><p style="text-align: left;page-break-after:auto" class="MsoNormal"><a name="_f85c2266-a8c5-c707-843e-2b9fc1ebbed7" id="_f85c2266-a8c5-c707-843e-2b9fc1ebbed7"></a><u>IHO Definition:</u> The distance between two successive peaks (or other points of identical phase) on an electromagnetic wave in the radar band of the electromagnetic spectrum.</p>

